Exploratory Data Analysis

There is a moderate correlation between family income and overall expenditure

## create new variable(s)
group6FilterIncome <- mutate(group6FilterIncome, ENT_EXP_IS_HIGH = ENTERTAINMENT_EXP >= 164)
group6FilterIncome <- mutate(group6FilterIncome, EMPLOYED = OCCU_REF != 0)
group6FilterIncome <- mutate(group6FilterIncome, GENDER = ifelse(SEX_REF == 1, "MALE" , "FEMALE"))
group6FilterIncome <- mutate(group6FilterIncome, OVERALL_EXP = ENTERTAINMENT_EXP + ELCTRC_EXP + FOOD_EXP + WATER_EXP + NAT_GAS_EXP + TRANS_EXP + HEALTH_EXP + TELEPH_EXP + EHOUS_EXP)
result <- correlation(
  group6FilterIncome, 
  vars = c("FAM_Income", "OVERALL_EXP")
)
summary(result)

Rural populations typically have lower household incomes than urban families
